  "texts": [
    "It is calculated by dividing the number of true positives by the sum of true positives and false positives [44,45,48,49] (see Eq. 6).",
    "RecallAlso known as sensitivity, it shows the ability of the classifier to display correct predictions [44,45,48] (see Eq. 7).",
    "( F1F1 is a metric used to assess the model's ability to accurately identify positive and negative cases.",
    "This metric is sensitive to imbalance.",
    "It is calculated as the harmonic mean between precision and recall [44,45,48,50] (see Eq. 8)."
